</head>
<body>

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>Fragrant & Delicious Pulao Recipe</h1>
        

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>1 cup Basmati Rice</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Ghee or Oil</li>
            <li>1 Bay Leaf</li>
            <li>2 Cloves</li>
            <li>1-inch Cinnamon Stick</li>
            <li>1 Cardamom</li>
            <li>1 Onion (sliced)</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Carrot (chopped)</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Peas</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Potato (diced)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Garam Masala</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
            <li>2 cups Water</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Wash and soak basmati rice for 20 minutes.</li>
            <li>Heat ghee in a pan and add bay leaf, cloves, cinnamon, and cardamom.</li>
            <li>Add cumin seeds and let them crackle.</li>
            <li>Add onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add chopped vegetables and cook for 2 minutes.</li>
            <li>Mix in turmeric powder, garam masala, and salt.</li>
            <li>Add soaked rice and sauté for 2 minutes.</li>
            <li>Pour 2 cups of water, cover, and cook for 10-12 minutes on low flame.</li>
            <li>Fluff the rice with a fork and serve hot with raita or curry.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
